FBIS4-40882 "drsov119_e_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-119 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Defense Minister Seeks Support From Chicago Community Defense Minister Seeks Support From Chicago Community LD2006164394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1500 GMT 20 Jun 94 LD2006164394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] The head of a Ukrainian military delegation, Defense Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy, has held several meetings in Washington's White House. Intensive talks at different levels have been held during the Ukrainian delegation's official visit to the United States, the Ukrainian Defense Ministry Press Service reports. In Chicago, Vitaliy Radetskyy and his colleagues were warmly greeted by the local Ukrainian community. In his address to its members, Radetskyy dwelled in detail on the course of Ukraine's army building. He stressed that the present state of military and technical capability in the Ukrainian Armed Forces is quite sufficient for the defense of the Ukrainian state. At the same time, Radetskyy pointed out the problems of servicemen's social protection. The most urgent of these, he said, is the housing problem, in the solving of which Ukraine could use, as far as possible, the assistance of the Ukrainian community in the United States.
